ist-item --><\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Read or write data from\/to Dataverse<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Trigger business logic<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Run queries and fetch related records<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Perform operations similar to SQL (using OData syntax)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>This is ideal for advanced integrations where direct, real-time communication with Dataverse is required.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>\u27a1\ufe0f <a class=\"\" href=\"https:\/\/learn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/power-apps\/developer\/data-platform\/webapi\/overview\">Use the Microsoft Dataverse Web API<\/a><br \/>\u27a1\ufe0f <a class=\"\" href=\"https:\/\/learn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/power-apps\/developer\/data-platform\/webapi\/reference\/about?view=dataverse-latest\">Full API Reference<\/a><\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:separator --><\/p>\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\" \/>\n<p><!-- \/wp:separator --><!-- wp:heading {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<h4>2. \u2699\ufe0f Power Automate<\/h4>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<h5>What is Power Automate?<\/h5>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p><strong>Power Automate<\/strong> is Microsoft\u2019s cloud-based automation platform that enables you to automate workflows across Microsoft 365 and hundreds of other applications without writing code.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>You can use Power Automate to:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:list --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Automate repetitive tasks like sending emails or syncing data<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Set up approval workflows (e.g., leave requests or budget sign-offs)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Trigger processes when records are created or updated in systems<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Schedule jobs or run flows based on conditions (e.g., only on weekdays)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>This tool is perfect for both business users and developers. It speeds up your processes, reduces manual effort, and increases accuracy.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>\u27a1\ufe0f <a class=\"\" href=\"https:\/\/learn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/power-automate\/\">Explore Power Automate (official site)<\/a><\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:separator --><\/p>\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\" \/>\n<p><!-- \/wp:separator --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<h5>Out-of-the-box connectors for third-party systems<\/h5>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>Power Automate includes <strong>hundreds of pre-built connectors<\/strong> to widely used platforms such as:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:list --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Salesforce<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>SharePoint<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Dropbox<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>SQL Server<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>SAP<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Google Drive<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Outlook<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Twitter<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Adobe PDF Services, and more<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>These <strong>out-of-the-box (OOB) connectors<\/strong> allow you to automate tasks across multiple apps with minimal setup\u2014no need to build custom code for every connection.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>\u27a1\ufe0f <a class=\"\" href=\"https:\/\/learn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/connectors\/connector-reference\/\">See the full list of connectors<\/a><\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:separator --><\/p>\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\" \/>\n<p><!-- \/wp:separator --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<h5>Create Custom Connectors in Power Automate<\/h5>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>If the system you&#8217;re working with doesn&#8217;t have a pre-built connector, Power Automate allows you to build a <strong>custom connector<\/strong>. These connectors are wrappers around any REST API you provide, giving your organization the flexibility to integrate nearly any web-based application into your flows.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>You can define:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:list --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Authentication methods (OAuth2, API keys, etc.)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Request parameters and response handling<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Actions and triggers that will be available inside Power Automate<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>\u27a1\ufe0f <a class=\"\" href=\"https:\/\/learn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/connectors\/custom-connectors\/\">Custom connectors overview<\/a><br \/>\u27a1\ufe0f <a class=\"\" href=\"https:\/\/learn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/connectors\/custom-connectors\/define-blank\">Create a custom connector from scratch<\/a><\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:separator --><\/p>\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\" \/>\n<p><!-- \/wp:separator --><!-- wp:heading {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<h4>3. \ud83d\uddc3\ufe0f Microsoft Dataverse<\/h4>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<h5>What is Dataverse\u2014and why is it special?<\/h5>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p><strong>Microsoft Dataverse<\/strong> is the secure, scalable data platform behind many Microsoft Power Platform applications (like Power Apps and Power Automate). Think of it as a <strong>cloud database built for business apps<\/strong>, complete with relational data modeling, field validation, role-based access, and auditing.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>Key benefits:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:list --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Deep integration with Microsoft 365 and Dynamics 365<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Tables, relationships, calculated fields, file storage<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Supports plug-ins, business rules, and automated flows<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Designed for both citizen developers and professional developers<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>If you\u2019re building internal tools or portals that need structured, secure, and scalable data storage, Dataverse is the platform to explore.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>\u27a1\ufe0f <a class=\"\" href=\"https:\/\/learn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/power-apps\/maker\/data-platform\/data-platform-intro\">What is Microsoft Dataverse?<\/a><\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:separator --><\/p>\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\" \/>\n<p><!-- \/wp:separator --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<h5>Role-based security controls<\/h5>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>Dataverse includes a <strong>robust security model<\/strong> that ensures data is only accessible to the right people. You can configure:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:list --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Security roles<\/strong>: Define who can create, read, update, or delete records<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Team-based access<\/strong>: Share permissions across functional groups<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Row-level and field-level security<\/strong>: Hide sensitive data from unauthorized users<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Environment-level isolation<\/strong>: Control access across development, test, and production environments<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>This makes Dataverse a good fit for organizations with privacy, compliance, or internal governance requirements.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>\u27a1\ufe0f <a class=\"\" href=\"https:\/\/learn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/power-platform\/admin\/security-roles-privileges\">Dataverse Security Roles &amp; Privileges<\/a><\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:separator --><\/p>\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\" \/>\n<p><!-- \/wp:separator --><!-- wp:heading {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<h4>\ud83d\udc4b Final Thoughts<\/h4>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} --><\/p>\n<p>Eve